## Finding: Performance Testing Does Not Cover API Contract Testing

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: There is no skill covering API contract testing (Pact, Spring Cloud Contract, Dredd). Contract testing ensures that API consumers and providers agree on the interface without needing to run the full stack. This is distinct from integration testing (which tests against a real running service) and is critical for microservices architectures where teams develop independently. The integration_testing skill covers Supertest against a running NestJS app but not contract-based consumer-driven testing.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill: `contract_testing` — covers consumer-driven contract testing with Pact (JavaScript), Spring Cloud Contract (Java), and schema validation patterns. Trigger: "contract test for [API/service]".
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 3 builds APIs that integrate_testing validates, but cross-service contracts are never verified. Phase 5 ships services that may break when deployed together.

