## Finding: Accessibility Testing Scope Is Too Narrow (Web Only, WCAG 2.1 Only)

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: The accessibility_testing skill covers WCAG 2.1 AA for web apps using axe-core, jest-axe, and Playwright. It does NOT cover: mobile accessibility (iOS VoiceOver, Android TalkBack, both mandatory for App Store compliance), desktop app accessibility (Windows Narrator, JAWS), WCAG 2.2 (the current standard, published September 2023 — the skill targets 2.1), European Accessibility Act (EAA) compliance deadlines (June 2025), Section 508 compliance for US government projects, or PDF/document accessibility. For a general-purpose framework, only covering web WCAG 2.1 is insufficient.
### Proposed Resolution: Update accessibility_testing to reference WCAG 2.2 (current), add WCAG 2.2 new success criteria (2.5.7 Dragging Movements, 2.5.8 Target Size, 3.2.6 Consistent Help, 3.3.7 Redundant Entry, 3.3.8 Accessible Authentication). Add a separate `mobile_accessibility` skill for iOS/Android.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Web apps ship to Phase 5 tested against an outdated standard. Mobile apps built in Phase 3 ship with no accessibility testing whatsoever.

