## Finding: SPEC — security_property_testing Addition to Existing Skills

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Confirmed in Loop 4 (tests verify functionality, not security properties), Loop 5 (E2E testing missing security user journeys).
### Proposed Resolution:
  Name: security_property_testing (new section added to integration_testing and e2e_testing skills)
  Phase: 4-secure
  Trigger Commands: "write security tests for [feature]", "test rate limiting", "test account lockout", "test CSRF protection", "Using security_property_testing: validate [security behavior]"
  Scope: Adds security property test patterns to integration_testing and e2e_testing skills. Integration level: rate limiting (assert 429 after N requests), account lockout (assert 423/429 after 5 failed logins), timing-attack-safe comparison verification (assert auth responses are within ±50ms of each other), CORS header validation, CSP header presence and value verification. E2E level: brute force protection flow (browser-level lockout), session expiry and re-auth flow, privilege escalation prevention (standard user accessing /admin routes), MFA enrollment and bypass prevention. Output: Security test suite additions to existing specs.
  Priority: P1 (High)
### Cross-Phase Impact: Bridges security_audit (manual) with automated testing. Ensures security properties remain tested in CI across all future changes.

